ome upon retirement the main types are immediate  allow you to be paid a set amount of money on a predetermined schedule fixed period annuities  are a more conservative option and come with a minimum interest rate guaranteed equityindexed  give you the opportunity to earn a higher rate of return variable annuities  the most flexible annuity and are subject to rises similar to stocks bonds or mutual funds from our customers your response was super timely and the agents to whom i spoke were very professional and helpful martha lewallen south bend in insurance corner  states will sue over health care bill passage thu  feb  —  states will sue over health care bill passageposted on mon march  news states will sue over health care bill read more  to go down as costly year for weather disasters thu  feb  —  to go down as costly year for weather disastersposted on thu january  news to go down as costly year for read more read more articles find information and get free insurance quotes fixed period annuities these are annuities that offer a set period of time for payback usually in ranges of  years  more information on fixed annuities variable annuities these are annuities that the money is invested into a mutual fund managed by the company  growth depends on the performance of the funds  more information on variable annuities nonqualified annuities these are annuities that are purchased through a tax deferred account but are not tax deductable and taxes must be paid on the income  more information on nonqualified annuities life annuities these are annuities that payout until the person is no longer alive  more information on life annuities qualified annuities these are annuities that are purchased through a tax deferred account such as a k and are tax deductable  more information on qualified annuities single premium annuities these annuities require an up front lump sum of money to get going  more information on single premium annuities get free insurance quotes and save 